			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Moontoast is a venture-backed start-up building the leading market solution that empowers brands to create, grow and measure meaningful relationships with their fans through social and mobile technologies. Our passionate, rapidly growing team is seeking a Marketing Associate to be responsible for the analysis of marketing campaigns and will be counted on to understand the dynamics of our business and sales cycle in order to steer top-level decisions that drive prospective clients to both our site and to our Moontoast solutions.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate is a self-starter with a combination of strong analytical and communication skills with a passion for understanding marketing channels and how they affect consumer acquisition and conversion. He or she must thrive in a fast-paced, results-oriented environment, pay great attention to detail, have strong intellectual curiosity, a roll-up-your-sleeves attitude, and a strong desire to succeed.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities-</p>
<ul>
<li>
Weekly and monthly reporting deliverables around a wide range of rigorous analytics related to ongoing marketing efforts.</li>
<li>
Evaluate the performance of several online &amp; offline marketing programs (including SEO/SEM, direct mail and online display advertising) and make recommendations to help improve marketing programs efficiencies.</li>
<li>
Develop and execute plans to improve website visit retention, conversion and user experience.</li>
<li>
Develop and manage email marketing and testing strategies geared towards prospective clients, leads and clients with particular focus on targeted and segmented messaging.</li>
<li>
Perform in-depth analyses on specific areas and issues and develop actionable findings.</li>
<li>
Provide analytical assistance to other team members and business units.</li>
<li>
Present analyses to both the marketing team and company executives.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Requirements-</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
A passion to learn and grow in a startup environment - a drive to take charge and make things happen.</li>
<li>
A love for data and understanding all that it can reveal. An ability to translate numbers into business insight and uncovering both, the what and the why.</li>
<li>
Advanced Excel abilities (pivot tables, charts, functions) with ability to spot trends and insights</li>
<li>
Good knowledge of marketing programs; experience with SEO, SEM, online conversion methodology, and LTV a plus.</li>
<li>
Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>
<li>
Ability to work comfortably and professionally in a dynamic, fast-paced and collaborative environment.</li>
<li>
Strong organizational and time management skills, ability to prioritize multiple assignments and meet all deadlines with minimal supervision and strong attention to detail.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Education/Other Pre-Requisites</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s degree with a strong academic record. Quant background in Marketing, Econ, Math, Engineering or Science is preferred but not mandatory.</li>
<li>
1-3 years of work experience, preferably in a marketing discipline. Online experience is a plus.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
