			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Moontoast has been named both an eCommerce and Music industry Cool Vendor by Gartner Research. Our passionate, rapidly growing product development team is seeking a talented Systems Engineer to be a part of a team of energetic, free-thinkers that move fast and take risks at the forefront of the social revolution.</p>
<p>
We deliver high profile, high visibility, branded social apps that are distributed through various social networks and content networks driving interactions and transactions. Our apps are built to be best-in-class, well-designed and intuitive user experiences by leveraging game mechanics and mobile design techniques to differentiate our SaaS-based product suite in the market.</p>
<p>
As a Facebook Preferred Marketing Developer, our social apps are recognized as best-in-class and Moontoast believes in creating well-designed and elegant app experiences. To continue to deliver on our goal of being the innovative leader in building and distributing social apps in social platforms, we need people who can work with new ideas and concepts effectively and execute on delivering on our go-to-market messaging and positioning.</p>
<p>
The Systems Engineer will report directly to the Director of Engineering and will work closely with engineering, operations and the management team to provide line support for product strategy, on-going sales support and operational readiness. As a rapidly growing company, we need someone who can keep up with our fast pace and help create innovative solutions to keep Moontoast the recognized leader in the social app and platform market space.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>f</strong>or administration of PCI Level 1 compliant e-commerce online applications</li>
<li>
for administering web applications under heavy load</li>
<li>
for maintaining and establishing systems operations processes</li>
<li>
for installation and maintenance of Nagios, Snort and other key Open Source systems management tools.</li>
<li>
for administration of Amazon Web Services based infrastructure</li>
<li>
for administration of tools like Puppet and Chef for server configuration and provisioning</li>
<li>
for administering Linux and writing shell scripts</li>
<li>
for working closely with developers to create solutions tailored to server environments</li>
<li>
for understanding of components and concepts of &ldquo;Web 2.0&rdquo; and &ldquo;real-time web&rdquo; applications</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree</li>
<li>
2+ years of experience administering enterprise systems</li>
<li>
Passionate about both social and mobile innovations</li>
<li>
Strong demonstrated writing and communication skills</li>
<li>
Understanding and interest in software development technologies</li>
<li>
Demonstrated results-oriented achievement as a creative thinker</li>
<li>
Ability to produce strong documentation</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>About Moontoast:</strong></p>
<p>
Moontoast is an emerging leader in social marketing, social commerce and social analytics. Moontoast&rsquo;s Social Activation Engine enables brands to effectively focus their social efforts on relationships, relevancy and results through a library of social engagement and commerce applications distributed on Facebook, Twitter, Pinterest, blogs and affiliate websites. Brands can directly measure social and transactional results using Moontoast&rsquo;s patent-pending Social Analytics Suite. Gartner Research has named Moontoast a &ldquo;Cool Vendor&rdquo; in Music and eCommerce, and Billboard Magazine called Moontoast a &ldquo;Top Startup of 2011.&rdquo;</p>
